---
import T7Layout from '../layouts/T7Layout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = 'Terms and Conditions';
const description =
  'Terms and Conditions for UK Mortgages Worldwide, a trading style of Sandsea Capital Ltd, an appointed representative of Quilter Financial Services Limited.';

const schemas = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Terms and Conditions' },
  ]),
];
---

<T7Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Terms and Conditions"
  eyebrow="LEGAL"
  schemas={schemas}
>
  <p><strong>YOUR HOME MAY BE REPOSSESSED IF YOU DO NOT KEEP UP REPAYMENTS ON YOUR MORTGAGE.</strong></p>

  <p>Effective Date: [APPROVAL DATE TBD]</p>

  <p>
    The guidance and information contained within this website is subject to
    the UK regulatory regime and is therefore intended for consumers based
    in the United Kingdom.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Legal Status and Regulatory Disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    UK Mortgages Worldwide is a trading style of Sandsea Capital Ltd, an
    appointed representative of Quilter Financial Services Limited, which
    is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority. Sandsea
    Capital Ltd is registered in England and Wales No. 11374947. Registered
    Office: 555-557 Cranbrook Road, Gants Hill, Ilford, Essex, England IG2
    6HE.
  </p>
  <p>Approver: Quilter Financial Services Limited [APPROVAL DATE TBD].</p>
  <p><strong>YOUR HOME MAY BE REPOSSESSED IF YOU DO NOT KEEP UP REPAYMENTS ON YOUR MORTGAGE.</strong></p>

  <h2>2. Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS)</h2>
  <p>
    UK Mortgages Worldwide does not provide or hold mortgage funds. We act
    solely as a mortgage intermediary, providing advice and arranging
    regulated mortgage and insurance products. Any lending obligations rest
    entirely with the mortgage lender and are governed by the lender's
    terms and conditions.
  </p>
  <p>
    In the event that we are unable to meet our obligations, clients may be
    entitled to compensation under the Financial Services Compensation
    Scheme (FSCS):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mortgage advice and arrangement:</strong> 100% of the first £85,000 (per eligible person, per firm).</li>
    <li><strong>Insurance advice and arrangement:</strong> 100% of the claim with no upper limit.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Eligibility criteria apply. For more information visit
    <a href="https://www.fscs.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.fscs.org.uk</a>
  </p>

  <h2>3. Scope of Agreement and Variation</h2>
  <p>
    The Terms of Business set out the basis on which we will provide
    services to you. This version will take effect upon receipt. We reserve
    the right to amend these Terms by providing you any revised terms,
    unless it is impractical to do so.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Instructions and Authority</h2>
  <p>
    Instructions may be provided to us verbally or in writing. All
    transactions will require completion of relevant documentation and
    signatures. Our authority to act on your behalf under these Terms can
    be terminated by either party at any time by written notice.
    Termination will not affect any rights or obligations already accrued
    or any transactions already in progress.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Conflicts of Interest</h2>
  <p>
    We maintain a Conflicts of Interest Policy in accordance with Financial
    Conduct Authority requirements. Where we or an associated party have a
    material interest in any transaction, we will disclose this to you in
    writing and obtain your informed consent before proceeding.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Record-Keeping and Access</h2>
  <p>
    We will maintain records of all client transactions in accordance with
    Financial Conduct Authority rules and UK data protection laws. Copies
    of relevant documents can be provided to you or your authorised
    representative upon written request.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Product Ownership and Documentation</h2>
  <p>
    As an intermediary, we never hold legal title to any product on your
    behalf. All products will be registered in your name. We will forward
    all documentation relating to ownership as soon as practicable after
    receipt from the provider. Some providers may send documents directly
    to you.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Reviews</h2>
  <p>
    We may contact you at a future date to review your arrangements,
    especially where it may be in your interest to revise or replace the
    original recommendation. Reviews are not guaranteed unless agreed as
    part of an ongoing service.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Client Money</h2>
  <p>
    We do not hold or accept client money. We do not accept cheques made
    payable to us (unless in settlement of an advice fee invoice), and we
    do not handle cash.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Fees and Charges</h2>
  <p>
    UK Mortgages Worldwide may charge a fee of up to £1,100 for advice in
    relation to mortgage and protection services. In most cases, this fee
    is waived. However, a fee may become payable where a formal mortgage
    offer has been secured, and you then choose not to proceed, for
    example, if you decide to instruct another broker.
  </p>
  <p>
    Full details of any applicable fees will be clearly outlined in our
    Initial Disclosure Document and your Authority to Proceed, which your
    adviser will provide and explain before any chargeable activity takes
    place.
  </p>
  <p>
    Please note that additional costs, charges, or taxes relating to your
    mortgage or protection arrangements may apply, which are not charged by
    or payable through UK Mortgages Worldwide.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Data Protection and Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    We are committed to protecting your personal data. Your information
    will be processed in accordance with the UK General Data Protection
    Regulation and the Data Protection Act 2018.
  </p>
  <p>
    Information you provide may be shared with Quilter Financial Services
    Limited, our professional adviser and selected third-party providers
    for regulatory, administrative or compliance purposes. We will only
    share your data where confidentiality and security are assured. For
    full details, please refer to the Quilter Appointed Representative
    Privacy Notice at
    <a href="https://www.quilter.com/important-information/privacy-notices/appointed-representative-privacy-notice/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.quilter.com/important-information/privacy-notices/appointed-representative-privacy-notice/</a>
  </p>

  <h2>12. Communications and Call Recording</h2>
  <p>
    All communications will be conducted in English. Telephone calls may
    be recorded for monitoring, training and regulatory purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Legal Jurisdiction</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. All
    communications will be conducted in English. The Contracts (Rights of
    Third Parties) Act 1999 shall not apply to this agreement.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Website Terms of Use</h2>
  <p>
    By accessing or using this website, you agree to be bound by the
    following terms:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The content is for general information purposes only and does not constitute financial advice.</li>
    <li>We strive to ensure accuracy, but information is subject to change without notice.</li>
    <li>No warranty or guarantee is given as to the accuracy, timeliness, performance, completeness or suitability of any material on this site.</li>
    <li>Use of any material is entirely at your own risk. It is your responsibility to ensure that products or services meet your specific requirements.</li>
    <li>This website and its content are protected by copyright. No part may be reproduced, copied or distributed without our prior written consent.</li>
    <li>You may not link to this website without written permission.</li>
    <li>Unauthorised use may give rise to a claim for damages or be a criminal offence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>15. Website Security and Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    Access to this website is provided on an "as is" and "as available"
    basis. We do not guarantee uninterrupted access or that the website is
    virus-free. While we take reasonable precautions, internet use carries
    inherent risks and users are responsible for securing their systems.
    We accept no liability for any loss or damage, direct or indirect,
    arising from website use.
  </p>

  <h2>16. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies and analytics tools to enhance the performance of our
    website and improve user experience. Cookies collect anonymous data
    and do not identify individuals. By using our website, you consent to
    the use of cookies in accordance with this policy.
  </p>

  <h2>17. Intellectual Property, Copyright and Trademarks</h2>
  <p>
    The material on our website is protected by copyright. This includes
    but is not limited to trademarks, branding, layout, design, and
    content. No part of it may in any form or by any means (electronic,
    mechanical, micro-copying, photocopying, recording, or otherwise) be
    reproduced, uploaded to a third party, linked to, framed, stored in a
    retrieval system or transmitted without our express written
    permission. You also must not in any form or by any means commercialise
    any information, products or services obtained from our website
    without our prior written permission. Our website includes registered
    trade marks owned by us or our licensors. You must not use any of our
    trademarks in any way without our express written consent.
  </p>

  <h2>18. External Links</h2>
  <p>
    This website may contain links to third-party websites. We do not
    endorse or guarantee the content or services provided on these
    external sites and accept no liability for their use.
  </p>

  <hr class="t7-divider" />

